parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer can lead to inaccurate speed readings, which can cause accidents, traffic violations, and safety hazards.
symptoms: The speedometer displays incorrect or erratic readings
stuck at a specific speed
or fails to register speed altogether.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can lead to inaccurate or missing readings of vital vehicle information, which can cause safety hazards and inconvenience.
symptoms: The instrument cluster gauges fail to work properly
display incorrect readings
or do not illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can lead to overheating, smoke, and fire hazards, which can cause accidents, injuries, and property damage.
symptoms: The air conditioning system produces extreme heat
smoke
or catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can lead to engine stalling, loss of power, and safety hazards.
symptoms: The check engine warning light remains illuminated
and the ignition switch needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shift indicator can lead to confusion, accidents, and safety hazards.
symptoms: The shift indicator is intermittent or not visible during vehicle operation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of brake lines can cause sudden brake failure, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal travels to the floorboard abnormally
loss of brake fluid
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
sudden failure of brakes
grinding or slipping feeling while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Aluminum Anti-Lock Distribution Box
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the aluminum anti-lock distribution box can cause brake failure, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake failure
corrosion of the aluminum anti-lock distribution box
brake lines rusted through
brake pedal travels to the floorboard abnormally.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature corrosion of brake components can cause brake failure, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Corrosion of brake lines
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
sudden failure of brakes
grinding or slipping feeling while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Gear Shift Selector Indicator
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear shift selector indicator can cause the driver to be unaware of the current gear, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The gear shift selector indicator light does not illuminate
the light is dim or faded
the indicator does not light up in stopped or moving positions
the driver is unable to determine the current gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slippage and failure can cause the vehicle to decelerate or lose power, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transmission slips into gear
the vehicle decelerates
the transmission fails to engage properly
the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transfer case noise and failure can cause the vehicle to vibrate or lose power, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: A bearing or ticking noise comes from the transfer case
the noise is audible when using 2H at high speeds
the noise goes away in auto 4-wheel mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: 4WD actuator failure can cause the vehicle to lose traction and stability, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The 4WD system fails to engage
the traction control system is disabled
the vehicle loses traction and stability.
